{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6ec3de16-ea16-4d93-96dc-f2b51293c027","content":"There's no pipeline file in the current directory, so here's the general guidance:\n\n## Migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n**1. Update your test project(s)**\n\nAdd the MTP runner and required extensions to each test `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<ItemGroup>\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n  <!-- TRX report output -->\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n  <!-- Code coverage -->\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\n**2. Replace the `VSTest@3` task**\n\nRemove:\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testSelector: 'testAssemblies'\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**\\*Tests.dll'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\nReplace with `dotnet test` (which invokes the new platform automatically once `Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild` is referenced):\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests (Microsoft.Testing.Platform)'\n  inputs:\n    command: 'test'\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --no-build\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      -- \n      --report-trx\n      --coverage\n      --coverage-output-format cobertura\n```\n\n**3. Publish results & coverage**\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish TRX results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: 'VSTest'\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/coverage.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key differences\n| | VSTest@3 | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | `vstest.console.exe` | Built into `dotnet test` |\n| TRX | Automatic | `--report-trx` flag |\n| Coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` | `--coverage` flag |\n| Config separator | N/A | `--` separates MSBuild args from platform args |\n\nArguments after `--` are passed directly to the testing platform (not MSBuild), which is where `--report-trx` and `--coverage` go.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"68740ea9-81ed-4f60-a62c-a48b30a412f1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There's no repository content here. The user is asking a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":736,"requestId":"9828:1CC26D:180AA3:1F1CFB:69FFD801"},"id":"50a59378-7042-4740-9d3c-315a8316d81c","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:57:51.461Z","parentId":"bf34802d-b2ae-460c-840a-df919a5a394e"}
